claim.claim-text:
1. A computer configured with a display device and at least one input device, for a single play of a card game, to:
(a) cause the display device to display a first hand of five cards face up to a player;
(b) enable none, one or more than one of the face up cards from the first hand to be held by the same player;
(c) display to the same player each held card from the first hand in each of a plurality of additional hands;
(d) complete each additional hand such that each additional hand has five displayed cards; and
(e) determine the poker hand ranking of the cards of each additional hand.

4. A method of operating a computer for a single play of a card game, said method comprising:
(a) causing one display device to display a first hand of a plurality of cards face up to a player;
(b) enabling none, one or more than one of the face up cards from the first hand to be held by the same player;
(c) displaying to the same player each held card from the first hand in each of a plurality of additional hands;
(d) completing each additional hand such that each additional hand has a designated quantity of displayed cards; and
(e) causing the computer to determine the poker hand ranking of the cards of each additional hand.

7. A computer configured with a display device and at least one input device, for a single play of a card game, to:
(a) cause the display device to display a first hand of a plurality of cards face up to a player;
(b) enable none, one or more than one of the face up cards from the first hand to be held by the same player;
(c) display to the same player each held card from the first hand in each of a plurality of additional hands;
(d) complete each additional hand such that each additional hand has a predetermined quantity of displayed cards; and
(e) determine the poker hand ranking of the cards of each additional hand.

10. A method of operating a computer for a single play of a card game, said method comprising:
(a) causing one display device to display a first hand of a plurality of cards face up to a player;
(b) enabling none, one or more than one of the face up cards from the first hand to be held by the same player;
(c) displaying to the same player each held card from the first hand in each of a plurality of additional hands;
(d) completing each additional hand such that each additional hand has a plurality of displayed cards; and
(e) causing the computer to determine the poker hand ranking of the cards of each additional hand.
